cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG 

The paper describes a method for automatically building 3D models of the human head using techniques in 3D surface image analysis. This involves facial landmarking using supervised machine learning, symmetry plane detection, template warping, and pose normalization. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
